# Areas of Agreement

- AI can influence workplace productivity.
- AI changes how employees perform their work.

---

# Areas of Disagreement

- Source A views AI as overwhelmingly beneficial.
- Source C argues AI offers little value.
- Source B presents productivity as dependent on context and implementation.

---

# Final Assessment

Source B provides the strongest research summary because it acknowledges both the advantages and limitations of AI adoption. Rather than presenting a one-sided argument, it recognizes that productivity outcomes depend on organizational factors such as implementation quality, employee training, and business context.

Sources A and C each focus primarily on one side of the discussion, making them less suitable for balanced research.

---

# Reflection

## What I Learned

Comparing multiple sources provides a more complete understanding of a topic than relying on a single perspective. Balanced research considers both supporting and conflicting evidence before reaching conclusions.

---

## What I'd Do Differently

Include peer-reviewed studies, industry reports, and real-world case studies to verify the claims made by each source and strengthen the overall evaluation.

